1
00:00:14,890 --> 00:00:16,433
(door squeaking)

2
00:00:20,229 --> 00:00:21,730
(creaking)

3
00:00:23,649 --> 00:00:24,900
Finally made it.

4
00:00:24,900 --> 00:00:27,486
Hey, Waver!

5
00:00:27,486 --> 00:00:29,029
No, no, not there.

6
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:30,864
Over here.

7
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:33,450
Grandpa, what are
you doing up there?

8
00:00:33,450 --> 00:00:37,329
Enough with the questions,
just come on up here.

9
00:00:37,329 --> 00:00:39,164
Let's talk for a while.

10
00:00:39,164 --> 00:00:40,666
He wants to talk?

11
00:00:40,666 --> 00:00:43,377
Why do we have
to talk on the roof?

12
00:00:43,377 --> 00:00:45,796
Grandpa, can't it wait a while?

13
00:00:45,796 --> 00:00:48,048
Oh, come on,
don't be like that.

14
00:00:49,550 --> 00:00:52,469
He really does like you, boy.

15
00:00:52,469 --> 00:00:56,181
Rider, come on, they're
just under my spell and‐‐

16
00:00:56,181 --> 00:00:57,641
Oh, go up there.

17
00:00:57,641 --> 00:01:00,060
The old man seems to have
something important he wants

18
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:01,395
to tell you.

19
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:06,275
Relax, boy, I'll patrol
the area and keep watch.

20
00:01:06,817 --> 00:01:08,652
Don't be shy.

21
00:01:08,652 --> 00:01:11,530
That's not the problem.

22
00:01:11,530 --> 00:01:13,490
(sighs)

23
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:15,993
(singing in Japanese)

24
00:01:21,290 --> 00:01:33,885
♪

25
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:51,713
I love it up here.

26
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:54,383
This is the best place
to catch the first rays

27
00:02:54,383 --> 00:02:56,176
of the morning sun.

28
00:02:59,096 --> 00:03:00,055
Take a seat.

29
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:04,518
Here, I even have
some coffee for you,

30
00:03:04,518 --> 00:03:05,727
it'll warm you up.

31
00:03:05,727 --> 00:03:08,939
Grandpa, just how long have
you been sitting up here?

32
00:03:08,939 --> 00:03:11,525
When I woke up this morning
and checked in on you,

33
00:03:11,525 --> 00:03:13,527
I saw you hadn't
made it back yet,

34
00:03:13,527 --> 00:03:15,320
so I thought I'd
take the opportunity

35
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:18,532
to watch the sun come up
while I waited for my grandson

36
00:03:18,532 --> 00:03:19,866
to come home.

37
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:25,330
When you were just a tyke,
we used to come up to the roof

38
00:03:25,330 --> 00:03:28,166
on clear nights
and stargaze all the time.

39
00:03:29,459 --> 00:03:30,419
Do you remember?

40
00:03:32,129 --> 00:03:33,046
Yeah, I guess.

41
00:03:34,172 --> 00:03:36,633
When Martha and I
decided to live in Japan,

42
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:38,635
we made sure to build
our house up here in

43
00:03:38,635 --> 00:03:40,846
the hills of Miyama
and built it with

44
00:03:40,846 --> 00:03:42,722
a large skylight,
so we could easily

45
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:44,683
gain access to the roof.

46
00:03:44,683 --> 00:03:48,186
We dreamed of sitting up here
gazing at the beautiful sky

47
00:03:48,186 --> 00:03:51,273
with our grandchildren
alongside us, entranced

48
00:03:51,273 --> 00:03:54,025
by the stars as
much as we were.

49
00:03:54,025 --> 00:03:55,277
We never thought our wish

50
00:03:55,277 --> 00:03:57,195
would actually
come true, though.

51
00:03:57,195 --> 00:03:58,780
(gasps)

52
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:02,367
In all these years,
our real grandchildren

53
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:05,829
never once came up here
to watch the sky with us.

54
00:04:05,829 --> 00:04:07,372
Sadly, whenever
I've come up here

55
00:04:07,372 --> 00:04:10,750
to stargaze, I've always
been alone until now.

56
00:04:12,711 --> 00:04:18,633
Now, Waver, you really
aren't our grandson, are you?

57
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:20,177
(gasps)

58
00:04:20,177 --> 00:04:23,638
♪

59
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:25,724
It's very strange,
the way Martha and I

60
00:04:25,724 --> 00:04:28,643
were so completely convinced
that you were actually part

61
00:04:28,643 --> 00:04:30,353
of our family.

62
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:32,898
To be honest, you were
a bit too nice to be

63
00:04:32,898 --> 00:04:34,065
our grandson.

64
00:04:34,065 --> 00:04:36,151
You really messed up there.

65
00:04:36,151 --> 00:04:39,488
♪

66
00:04:39,488 --> 00:04:41,907
I suppose you're pretty mad.

67
00:04:41,907 --> 00:04:46,244
Well, I guess I probably
have every right to be, Waver.

68
00:04:46,244 --> 00:04:48,747
But lately, Martha's
been acting so happy

69
00:04:48,747 --> 00:04:52,250
and smiling nearly
every moment of every day.

70
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:55,086
I couldn't have imagined
her like that before.

71
00:04:55,086 --> 00:04:58,173
Really, I'm very grateful
to the both of you.

72
00:04:58,173 --> 00:05:00,258
It's been quite a blessing.

73
00:05:00,258 --> 00:05:02,928
Besides, it doesn't seem
to me you decided to move in

74
00:05:02,928 --> 00:05:04,805
with Martha and I
because you intended

75
00:05:04,805 --> 00:05:06,097
to cause us any harm.

76
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:09,893
So, what do you think?

77
00:05:11,728 --> 00:05:13,814
If you can, Martha and I
would really like it

78
00:05:13,814 --> 00:05:16,441
if you'd stay with
us a while longer.

79
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:19,945
♪

80
00:05:19,945 --> 00:05:23,323
I'm sorry,
I can't promise that.

81
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:26,701
I can't even guarantee I'll
make it back here safely.

82
00:05:26,701 --> 00:05:30,539
So, I gather you two
are risking your lives?

83
00:05:30,539 --> 00:05:32,123
Yes.

84
00:05:32,123 --> 00:05:34,376
Well, I can't even begin
to venture a guess as

85
00:05:34,376 --> 00:05:37,629
to how important whatever
it is you're doing is to you,

86
00:05:37,629 --> 00:05:39,923
but when you've had
a long life like me

87
00:05:39,923 --> 00:05:41,341
and look back on it all,

88
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:43,969
you come to realize that
there is absolutely nothing

89
00:05:43,969 --> 00:05:47,138
in this world so valuable
or so important that it's

90
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:50,225
really worth risking
that life for.

91
00:05:50,225 --> 00:05:56,690
♪

92
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:07,993
♪

93
00:06:07,993 --> 00:06:09,661
I guess it's been
about 40 hours

94
00:06:09,661 --> 00:06:12,455
since I last slept...maybe more.

95
00:06:13,832 --> 00:06:16,418
To win the battle
and summon the grail,

96
00:06:16,418 --> 00:06:19,671
one must perform the ritual
at the location of one of

97
00:06:19,671 --> 00:06:21,089
the four Fuyuki ley lines.

98
00:06:22,299 --> 00:06:26,386
At two of them, the church
and the Tohsaka Estate,

99
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:29,431
Kirei Kotomine
was nowhere to be found,

100
00:06:29,431 --> 00:06:31,099
which leaves the other two:

101
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:34,978
Here at Mt. Enzo and
the Fuyuki Citizens Building.

102
00:06:34,978 --> 00:06:36,980
Given the ley lines'
relative power,

103
00:06:36,980 --> 00:06:38,690
this one is more likely.

104
00:06:38,690 --> 00:06:41,192
Even if he's chosen
the Citizens Building,

105
00:06:41,192 --> 00:06:43,612
I can launch
a frontal assault there.

106
00:06:43,612 --> 00:06:45,447
♪

107
00:06:45,447 --> 00:06:48,491
If Maiya were still alive,
I would have sent her

108
00:06:48,491 --> 00:06:49,826
to secure it.

109
00:06:49,826 --> 00:06:53,872
♪

110
00:06:53,872 --> 00:06:56,666
Once again, I'm all alone.

111
00:06:56,666 --> 00:07:02,881
♪

112
00:07:02,881 --> 00:07:06,468
Come to think of it,
I never really figured her

113
00:07:06,468 --> 00:07:07,969
into my plans.

114
00:07:07,969 --> 00:07:12,349
♪

115
00:07:12,349 --> 00:07:14,643
Since last night,
I've been searching

116
00:07:14,643 --> 00:07:17,395
the whole city
for Irisviel's location,

117
00:07:17,395 --> 00:07:21,107
but I found no sign of her.

118
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:22,817
I am deeply sorry.

119
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:27,405
(splash)

120
00:07:27,405 --> 00:07:29,783
Well, then, if you need me,

121
00:07:29,783 --> 00:07:32,494
summon me using
the command seal.

122
00:07:48,927 --> 00:07:50,095
Wake up.

123
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,265
Can you hear me, woman?

124
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:58,561
♪

125
00:07:58,561 --> 00:08:01,648
So, it's you, Kirei.

126
00:08:01,648 --> 00:08:04,693
This building was once
the place where Caster's

127
00:08:04,693 --> 00:08:07,737
young master hid,
though it appears

128
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:11,950
that Kiritsugu Emiya
was never able to locate it.

129
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:14,994
Soon, the Holy
Grail War will be over.

130
00:08:14,994 --> 00:08:16,913
It's likely that I'll be the one

131
00:08:16,913 --> 00:08:18,456
that will have
the power to grant

132
00:08:18,456 --> 00:08:20,250
the wish of the Einzberns.

133
00:08:21,543 --> 00:08:24,379
Are you so unhappy
that it would be me?

134
00:08:24,379 --> 00:08:27,632
There is but one man to whom
I would entrust the grail,

135
00:08:27,632 --> 00:08:30,885
and it is certainly
not you, Inquisitor.

136
00:08:32,387 --> 00:08:37,475
Kiritsugu Emiya has already
seen right through you, Kirei.

137
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:41,020
He recognizes you as his
most dangerous enemy.

138
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:42,439
You can't escape.

139
00:08:42,439 --> 00:08:44,858
Your words are as
the gospel to my ears.

140
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:48,194
Kiritsugu Emiya is exactly

141
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:51,406
as I imagined him
to be after all.

142
00:08:51,406 --> 00:08:53,491
How laughable.

143
00:08:53,491 --> 00:08:57,829
You couldn't be any further
from him if you tried.

144
00:08:57,829 --> 00:08:59,330
What did you say?

145
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:01,958
Even though Kiritsugu
can see through you,

146
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:04,794
the reverse is impossible.

147
00:09:04,794 --> 00:09:07,547
You have none of
the wonderful things

148
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:10,800
that he carries deep
inside his heart.

149
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,344
Why do you speak of me
in such a manner, woman?

150
00:09:14,888 --> 00:09:17,766
I freely admit it,
I'm a man who is empty

151
00:09:17,766 --> 00:09:19,601
and desolate inside.

152
00:09:19,601 --> 00:09:22,187
So, how do he and I differ?

153
00:09:22,187 --> 00:09:24,981
Devoted himself to one
fruitless war after another

154
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:26,316
for years?

155
00:09:26,316 --> 00:09:28,276
Senseless slaughter,
utter recklessness,

156
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:29,569
wasted effort?!

157
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:32,197
If he does not doubt
or find this life

158
00:09:32,197 --> 00:09:34,240
pointless as I do,
then what is he?

159
00:09:36,284 --> 00:09:37,410
(coughing)

160
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:42,582
Tell me, what is his wish?

161
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:45,251
What would he ask
of the Holy Grail?

162
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:49,964
What prayer would he entrust
to the wish‐granting device?

163
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:52,008
(heavy breathing)

164
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:56,971
Very well, I'll tell you.

165
00:09:58,056 --> 00:10:01,434
Kiritsugu Emiya's wish

166
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:04,145
is humanity's salvation,

167
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:05,897
an end to all warfare

168
00:10:05,897 --> 00:10:09,025
and bloodshed and suffering...

169
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:09,859
forever.

170
00:10:11,069 --> 00:10:12,612
True peace upon the Earth.

171
00:10:14,656 --> 00:10:15,824
(light grunting)

172
00:10:18,743 --> 00:10:19,828
What was that?

173
00:10:20,954 --> 00:10:23,414
You can never understand it.

174
00:10:23,414 --> 00:10:26,417
That is the difference
between you two;

175
00:10:26,417 --> 00:10:28,336
he has something
to believe in.

176
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:31,589
(shudders)

177
00:10:31,589 --> 00:10:33,842
Conflict is
intrinsic to humanity.

178
00:10:35,260 --> 00:10:38,096
To eliminate it
completely would mean

179
00:10:38,096 --> 00:10:40,890
the elimination
of humanity itself.

180
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:44,102
As an ideal,
it's totally futile,

181
00:10:44,102 --> 00:10:46,938
nonsense that
a child would spout.

182
00:10:46,938 --> 00:10:50,441
Yes, and that is why
his only hope is for

183
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:51,568
a true miracle.

184
00:10:52,819 --> 00:10:56,656
Many times, Kiritsugu
has been forced to...

185
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:59,576
to sacrifice the lives
of people he's loved

186
00:10:59,576 --> 00:11:00,743
because of his beliefs.

187
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:06,749
Yes, you see, he's far
too kind to chase ideals.

188
00:11:08,626 --> 00:11:11,087
He must love even knowing

189
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:13,339
it will mean losing that love.

190
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:16,384
I understand.

191
00:11:18,386 --> 00:11:20,138
(whimpering)

192
00:11:20,138 --> 00:11:26,019
♪

193
00:11:26,019 --> 00:11:28,855
(grunting)

194
00:11:28,855 --> 00:11:35,320
♪

195
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:36,863
(snapping)

196
00:11:36,863 --> 00:11:47,916
♪

197
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:49,751
I understand well.

198
00:11:49,751 --> 00:11:51,878
So, that is Kiritsugu Emiya.

199
00:11:51,878 --> 00:11:57,258
♪

200
00:11:57,258 --> 00:12:01,054
At last, I see it,
my reason for fighting.

201
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:04,224
♪

202
00:12:04,224 --> 00:12:07,477
Kiritsugu Emiya,
I shall grind your ideals

203
00:12:07,477 --> 00:12:11,105
to dust right before you,
along with the Holy Grail

204
00:12:11,105 --> 00:12:12,440
you long for.

205
00:12:17,654 --> 00:12:20,240
(clock ticking)

206
00:12:37,966 --> 00:12:40,635
Oh, you finally woke up, boy.

207
00:12:40,635 --> 00:12:42,053
I thought I told
you to wake me up

208
00:12:42,053 --> 00:12:43,721
at nightfall.

209
00:12:43,721 --> 00:12:44,889
Did you forget?

210
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:47,642
Oh, sorry, but I thought
it might be good to take

211
00:12:47,642 --> 00:12:49,811
our time with preparations.

212
00:12:49,811 --> 00:12:53,398
Tonight, there is
no reason to rush.

213
00:12:53,398 --> 00:12:55,441
How come?

214
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:58,444
I can't say why exactly.

215
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:01,364
It feels like everything
will be concluding tonight.

216
00:13:02,573 --> 00:13:03,741
Uh‐huh.

217
00:13:03,741 --> 00:13:06,244
The night air
seems way too still.

218
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:09,998
Is that because there
are fewer participants

219
00:13:09,998 --> 00:13:12,000
still in the fight?

220
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,918
(globe spinning)

221
00:13:16,296 --> 00:13:18,589
From now on,
only the truly strong

222
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:20,383
remain in the battle.

223
00:13:20,383 --> 00:13:22,802
(bursts)

224
00:13:25,096 --> 00:13:27,265
W‐what was that?

225
00:13:27,265 --> 00:13:29,976
It's a very strange mana surge.

226
00:13:29,976 --> 00:13:32,395
I felt something
similar before.

227
00:13:32,395 --> 00:13:34,814
(bursts)

228
00:13:37,442 --> 00:13:38,776
Look at that pattern.

229
00:13:38,776 --> 00:13:41,654
What is it... some kind
of secret code, do you think?

230
00:13:41,654 --> 00:13:44,490
Four and seven
in different colors.

231
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:46,159
"Success and victory."

232
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:48,661
If they're
sending up that signal...

233
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:50,955
...does that mean that
someone got the grail

234
00:13:50,955 --> 00:13:52,165
and the war is over?

235
00:13:53,041 --> 00:13:54,625
No, it's coming up from

236
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:55,877
a completely
different direction

237
00:13:55,877 --> 00:13:58,629
than the church is,
which means that the church

238
00:13:58,629 --> 00:14:00,506
didn't send the message.

239
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:02,800
In essence, somebody
is getting way ahead

240
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:05,344
of themselves and claiming
to be victorious.

241
00:14:06,804 --> 00:14:08,473
That says, "If you object,

242
00:14:08,473 --> 00:14:09,891
come and get me!"

243
00:14:09,891 --> 00:14:11,476
It is an obvious challenge.

244
00:14:12,310 --> 00:14:14,145
It looks like
the big showdown

245
00:14:14,145 --> 00:14:15,396
is going to happen tonight.

246
00:14:17,315 --> 00:14:21,152
I see, that means
this is it, then.

247
00:14:21,819 --> 00:14:22,820
Quite right, boy!

248
00:14:24,906 --> 00:14:27,283
Now that we have
our battlefield,

249
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:31,496
I must go forth and bring honor
to the rider class and ride

250
00:14:31,496 --> 00:14:33,915
gloriously into
the final fray!

251
00:14:33,915 --> 00:14:35,041
(zapping)

252
00:14:35,041 --> 00:14:37,418
Come now, my steed!

253
00:14:37,418 --> 00:14:39,587
(zapping)

254
00:14:39,587 --> 00:14:42,048
(neighing)

255
00:14:44,050 --> 00:14:47,303
Now then, boy, it may
not be as smooth a ride

256
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:49,222
as by chariot, but‐‐Huh?

257
00:14:50,014 --> 00:14:52,225
Hey, what are you waiting for?

258
00:14:52,225 --> 00:14:53,101
Come on!

259
00:14:54,769 --> 00:14:57,188
From this point,
only the truly strong

260
00:14:57,188 --> 00:14:58,856
can continue, right?

261
00:14:58,856 --> 00:15:03,820
♪

262
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:06,823
My servant, Rider,
by his command seal,

263
00:15:06,823 --> 00:15:09,200
Waver Velvet orders you...

264
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:12,703
fight until you attain
the victory you seek.

265
00:15:12,703 --> 00:15:15,498
♪

266
00:15:15,498 --> 00:15:18,292
And by my command seal,
I further order that you,

267
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:20,962
Rider, go now
and win the Holy Grail.

268
00:15:20,962 --> 00:15:23,548
♪

269
00:15:23,548 --> 00:15:27,301
And by command seal,
I further order, Rider,

270
00:15:27,301 --> 00:15:29,053
take the world for your own.

271
00:15:29,053 --> 00:15:30,805
I will not tolerate failure.

272
00:15:30,805 --> 00:15:34,642
♪

273
00:15:34,642 --> 00:15:36,936
There, it's all over.

274
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:38,396
I'm no longer your master.

275
00:15:40,398 --> 00:15:42,984
Go, go wherever you wish.

276
00:15:44,443 --> 00:15:45,945
I don't even wanna see you.

277
00:15:47,071 --> 00:15:48,698
(grunts)

278
00:15:48,698 --> 00:15:49,907
(yelps)

279
00:15:49,907 --> 00:15:52,702
I'll certainly be
on my way in a moment,

280
00:15:52,702 --> 00:15:55,746
but after all those
annoying orders you just gave,

281
00:15:55,746 --> 00:15:58,749
surely you're prepared to
see this though to the end?

282
00:15:58,749 --> 00:16:01,127
You total idiot, listen to me!

283
00:16:01,127 --> 00:16:03,838
I used the command seals
and quit being your master!

284
00:16:03,838 --> 00:16:05,590
Why would you still
wanna take me, dammit?!

285
00:16:07,383 --> 00:16:08,259
I'm not your‐‐

286
00:16:08,259 --> 00:16:11,345
Master or not, boy,
you are still my friend

287
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:13,097
and always will be.

288
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:14,515
Huh?

289
00:16:14,515 --> 00:16:16,350
(chuckles)

290
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:18,644
♪

291
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:20,730
I'm...you mean...

292
00:16:20,730 --> 00:16:23,482
you're really
okay with me?

293
00:16:23,482 --> 00:16:26,360
You want someone
like me by your side?

294
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:27,445
What are you saying?

295
00:16:27,445 --> 00:16:29,739
After all the battles you
and I have seen together,

296
00:16:29,739 --> 00:16:31,240
you have to ask that?

297
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:32,241
Idiot.

298
00:16:32,241 --> 00:16:33,826
(neighing)

299
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:35,828
Up until now,
have you not faced

300
00:16:35,828 --> 00:16:37,788
the same enemies as I have?

301
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:39,624
That means you're my friend.

302
00:16:39,624 --> 00:16:42,793
So, be proud
and consider yourself

303
00:16:42,793 --> 00:16:44,128
my equal.

304
00:16:44,128 --> 00:16:47,506
♪

305
00:16:47,506 --> 00:16:48,716
(blows nose)

306
00:16:50,301 --> 00:16:53,471
All right, I shall begin
by obeying the first

307
00:16:53,471 --> 00:16:54,931
of your orders.

308
00:16:54,931 --> 00:16:57,308
Now, boy, keep your
eyes open to the end!

309
00:16:59,227 --> 00:17:00,228
(neighing)

310
00:17:00,228 --> 00:17:01,896
Well, let's see
what she can do.

311
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:04,732
Right before my open eyes!

312
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:08,486
(neighing)

313
00:17:08,486 --> 00:17:16,744
♪

314
00:17:16,744 --> 00:17:19,288
(bursts)

315
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:25,753
(engine puttering)

316
00:17:25,753 --> 00:17:27,338
He chose the place
least suited to

317
00:17:27,338 --> 00:17:29,173
the required ritual

318
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:32,468
only to gain the early
initiative in battle.

319
00:17:32,468 --> 00:17:36,889
In other words, his plan
is not to obtain the grail,

320
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:39,976
but rather to use it as bait

321
00:17:39,976 --> 00:17:41,435
to lure me and
the other masters

322
00:17:41,435 --> 00:17:44,021
into a trap,
then kill us all.

323
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:48,693
♪

324
00:17:48,693 --> 00:17:50,736
That simplifies things.

325
00:17:50,736 --> 00:17:53,573
If he's going to be
this incompetent,

326
00:17:53,573 --> 00:17:56,117
I'll just outmaneuver
and eliminate him quickly.

327
00:17:56,117 --> 00:17:59,120
♪

328
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:00,496
Kirei Kotomine.

329
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:05,751
♪

330
00:18:05,751 --> 00:18:07,670
Hm, very impressive.

331
00:18:07,670 --> 00:18:08,838
I must say, you look

332
00:18:08,838 --> 00:18:11,841
particularly ferocious
tonight, Kirei.

333
00:18:13,676 --> 00:18:15,678
Now what will you do?

334
00:18:15,678 --> 00:18:18,389
Do you wish for me
to stay here and wait?

335
00:18:18,389 --> 00:18:21,267
Unleashing all of your
power at this close range

336
00:18:21,267 --> 00:18:24,478
could endanger
the ceremony itself.

337
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:26,981
If you want to fight it
full strength you'll have

338
00:18:26,981 --> 00:18:28,649
to go out and meet them.

339
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:30,484
Very well, what if this place

340
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:33,029
falls under attack
while I'm gone?

341
00:18:33,029 --> 00:18:35,698
Will you allow me
to utilize the command seals

342
00:18:35,698 --> 00:18:37,074
to save myself?

343
00:18:37,074 --> 00:18:41,495
I will, but I do not guarantee
the Holy Grail's safety.

344
00:18:41,495 --> 00:18:44,415
For tonight,
I shant be holding back.

345
00:18:44,415 --> 00:18:46,542
That would be
the worst outcome,

346
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:47,877
but if that should happen,

347
00:18:47,877 --> 00:18:49,670
it will be fate.

348
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:54,550
Kirei, you seem to have finally
found your reason to fight,

349
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:57,845
but have you still no prayer
to offer the Holy Grail?

350
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:02,308
I can think of
nothing I want.

351
00:19:02,308 --> 00:19:05,770
My only hope is that nothing
will interfere with the conduct

352
00:19:05,770 --> 00:19:08,522
of the battle
we're about to enter.

353
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:10,900
Honestly, Kirei,
as I suspected,

354
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:14,320
the only recourse is to let
the grail reveal what hides

355
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:15,988
within your heart.

356
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:19,617
♪

357
00:19:19,617 --> 00:19:22,912
Oh, if it appears as if
Saber will be arriving here

358
00:19:22,912 --> 00:19:25,790
before I can return,
just have Berserker

359
00:19:25,790 --> 00:19:27,458
entertain her for
a little while.

360
00:19:28,584 --> 00:19:30,294
Understood.

361
00:19:30,294 --> 00:19:32,838
Speaking of Saber,
what happened to

362
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:35,966
the doll that was
so important to her?

363
00:19:35,966 --> 00:19:39,970
The Holy Grail's vessel
is inside of her, is it not?

364
00:19:41,472 --> 00:19:43,599
I took her life.

365
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:46,894
I had no reason to let
her continue living.

366
00:19:46,894 --> 00:19:48,688
(chuckles)

367
00:19:48,688 --> 00:19:53,526
♪

368
00:19:58,447 --> 00:20:10,543
♪

369
00:20:10,543 --> 00:20:12,920
(sobbing)

370
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:15,339
Are you crying?

371
00:20:15,339 --> 00:20:17,299
Are you, Mother?

372
00:20:17,299 --> 00:20:20,886
Hey, Mother,
I had a scary dream.

373
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:23,848
I dreamed that I
turned into a cup,

374
00:20:23,848 --> 00:20:27,059
and then I dreamed that
these seven gigantic lumps

375
00:20:27,059 --> 00:20:29,228
started to come into my body.

376
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:31,355
It's okay, it's okay.

377
00:20:32,523 --> 00:20:34,734
I would never
let that happen.

378
00:20:34,734 --> 00:20:37,695
I promise that will never
happen to you, Illya.

379
00:20:39,530 --> 00:20:42,032
I know in my heart
that you'll be released

380
00:20:42,032 --> 00:20:43,826
from the shackles of fate.

381
00:20:43,826 --> 00:20:50,875
♪

382
00:20:50,875 --> 00:20:52,752
(screeching)

383
00:20:55,212 --> 00:20:56,714
(gasps)

384
00:20:56,714 --> 00:21:00,968
♪

385
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:02,303
Where am I?

386
00:21:04,638 --> 00:21:06,640
Inside the Holy Grail?

387
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,893
This shouldn't be happening!

388
00:21:08,893 --> 00:21:10,352
(yelps)

389
00:21:18,694 --> 00:21:22,490
If I'm here...

390
00:21:22,490 --> 00:21:25,034
who am I?

391
00:21:29,538 --> 00:21:39,423
♪

392
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:43,928
That's right, this is
inside the Holy Grail:

393
00:21:43,928 --> 00:21:45,763
The omnipotent
wish‐granting device

394
00:21:45,763 --> 00:21:48,599
that will dispel all
the world's sadness

395
00:21:48,599 --> 00:21:50,184
and remove all
its suffering.

396
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:53,687
I will have the power
to make that happen.

397
00:21:54,772 --> 00:21:59,527
The end is nearly at hand.

398
00:21:59,527 --> 00:22:04,281
♪

399
00:23:37,791 --> 00:23:40,794
Our enemy is
the mighty King of Heroes,

400
00:23:40,794 --> 00:23:42,838
a most worthy opponent!

401
00:23:42,838 --> 00:23:45,507
Our noble path
of ultimate conquest!

402
00:23:45,507 --> 00:23:48,218
King of Conquerors,
know the end of your

403
00:23:48,218 --> 00:23:49,303
eternal dream.

404
00:23:49,303 --> 00:23:52,097
I shall show you
the stark reality.

